From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Keyur Maru <kd2maru@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 13 Jul 2026 05:28:11 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] libsysutils: build a recovery variant

LineageOS recovery links libvolume_manager, which is recovery_available and
depends on libsysutils. Without a recovery variant the recovery build fails to
resolve the dependency. All of libsysutils' own dependencies are already
recovery_available, so this only adds the variant.
---
 libsysutils/Android.bp | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

diff --git a/libsysutils/Android.bp b/libsysutils/Android.bp
index 18a6aa655..f4642c9b8 100644
--- a/libsysutils/Android.bp
+++ b/libsysutils/Android.bp
@@ -5,6 +5,9 @@ package {
 cc_library {
     name: "libsysutils",
     vendor_available: true,
+    // channel: LineageOS recovery's libvolume_manager (recovery_available) links
+    // this, so it needs a recovery variant. All deps are already recovery_available.
+    recovery_available: true,
 
     srcs: [
         "src/SocketListener.cpp",
